The Semantic Pivot Logic (SPL) is an original architectural framework designed to solve English syntactic ambiguity and reclaim the browsing experience from "Generative Slop." Instead of relying on predictive AI models that guess user intent, the SPL utilizes Logographic Pivoting to anchor search results to verified, real-world metadata.
â€‹This tool acts as a logic-driven filter, stripping away AI-generated summaries, sponsored noise, and conversational "bloat" to deliver a high-contrast, entity-first view of the internet.
